ons have adequate length with code examples included. I'm also confirming that all the key concepts mentioned in the hints (the error handler, exception classes, HTTP error responses, and execution context) are properly covered throughout. I'm reconsidering whether `ClientSearchForm` should be flagged as a missing hint since it's specific to the code example, whereas `HttpRequest` and `HttpResponse` are generic framework classes that wouldn't be useful discriminators. The knowledge file appears solid overall with just this one minor potential gap.\n\nNow checking the official documentation URLs—the file references the main page plus javadocs for `NoDataException`, `OptimisticLockException`, and `ApplicationException`, all of which are actually cited in the source material. The file looks clean with no critical issues to report.\n\nFor the hints section, I'm noticing that `ClientSearchForm` and `HttpResponse` appear in the s2 code example but aren't captured in the current hints, which list `ApplicationException`, `HttpErrorResponse`, `@InjectForm`, and `@OnError`. Since `ClientSearchForm` is a specific class name that would help locate this section, I'll flag it as a minor finding worth noting.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13805,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13805,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b6f40fe-f7f3-4f58-8498-75fff88aff77","uuid":"373edd0a-030e-4ba6-9b74-717284dfbef2"}
